doc/source/specs/ussuri/blazar-preemptib.message:
I don't think so.

If the starting reservation is host reservation, yes any instance on that host must be preemptible, but if the starting reservation is instance reservation, (some of) the autochthon instances can be reserved instances i.e. non-preemtible. 

I think we need a logic here like;

  if host_reservation:
      terminate_all_the_instances_on_the_host()
  else:
      terminate_preemptible_instances()

It might be an implementation matter whether we terminate all the *preemptible* instances in terminate_preemptible_instances() or just terminate only ones that can release enough resources for starting reservation.
